    <pw:title>
      Learning from Experience
    </pw:title>
    <pw:file-name>
      learning_from_experience
    </pw:file-name>
    <pw:body>
      <p>
        The most powerful learning comes from direct experience. But what happens when we can no longer observe the consequences of our actions? Herein lies the core <i>learning dilemma</i> that confronts organizations:<i> we learn best from experience but we never directly experience the consequences of many of our most important decisions.</i> The most critical decisions made in organizations have systemwide consequences that stretch over years or decades.
      </p>
